parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake assist system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to extended stopping distances and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor with little to no braking power
the vehicle takes longer to stop
warning lights appear on the dashboard including "Service Brake Assist"
"Service Stabilitrak"
and "ABS".

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag system can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the air bags may not deploy or deploy late, leaving occupants unprotected.
symptoms: Air bags do not deploy or deploy late in the event of a crash
error messages appear on the dashboard
air bag warning lights illuminate
air bags deploy unnecessarily (e.g.
due to a pothole).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays or inadequate responses to recalls can put drivers and passengers at risk, as they may continue to operate vehicles with known safety defects.
symptoms: Dealerships or manufacturers fail to prioritize recall repairs
leaving customers to drive vehicles with known safety issues
inadequate communication or lack of urgency from manufacturers or dealerships regarding recall repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping and Cruise Control Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and cruise control failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, and may result in costly repairs.
symptoms: Transmission slipping
cruise control not operating correctly
elevated RPM
check engine warning light illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of the clutch can cause difficulty shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, and may result in costly repairs.
symptoms: Clutch failure
difficulty shifting gears
clutch pedal feels soft or spongy.
